'''Juan Viedma''' is a [[paralympic]] [[track and field|athlete]] from [[Spain]] competing mainly in category F11 long and triple jump events.

Juan has competed in four paralympics starting with his home games in Spain in [[1992 Summer Paralympics|1992]].  He competed in the pentathlon and 100m before winning a silver in the long jump and gold in the triple jump.  The following games in [[1996 Summer Paralympics|1996]] he defended his triple jump gold medal but could only manage bronze in the long jump.  [[2000 Summer Paralympics|2000]] saw him fail to medal in either of the jumps but he was part of the bronze medal winning 4x100m relay team for Spain.  He returned for a fourth games in [[1996 Summer Paralympics|1996]]  where he competed in the long and triple jump but was unable to add any further medals.
